sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Gateway / Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant RBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Predictor as Model Server Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: InferenceService Model Serving (Raw Kubernetes)
    Client->>GW: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW->>RBAC: Forward to Service<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    RBAC->>Predictor: Proxy to container<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod-local)
    Predictor->>Storage: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, Provider credentials
    Storage-->>Predictor: Model artifacts
    Predictor-->>RBAC: Prediction result
    RBAC-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>Client: JSON Response

    participant GW2 as Gateway (HTTPRoute)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant EPP as Scheduler EPP<br/>gRPC/TCP TLS
    participant vLLM as vLLM Workload<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService with Gateway API
    Client->>GW2: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW2->>EPP: Route via InferencePool<br/>gRPC, TLS (self-signed), Bearer token
    EPP->>vLLM: Forward to workload<br/>HTTPS/8000, TLS (self-signed)
    vLLM->>S3: Fetch model<br/>HTTPS/443, Provider credentials
    S3-->>vLLM: Model data
    vLLM-->>EPP: Completion response
    EPP-->>GW2: Response
    GW2-->>Client: Streaming/JSON Response

    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Reencrypt
    participant Router as kserve-router<br/>8080/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant ISVC1 as InferenceService A<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant ISVC2 as InferenceService B<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client,ISVC2: Flow 3: InferenceGraph Routing (Ensemble)
    Client->>Route: POST /inference<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth/Token
    Route->>Router: TLS Reencrypt<br/>HTTPS/8080 or HTTP
    par Parallel Ensemble Execution
        Router->>ISVC1: Inference request<br/>HTTP/80, in-mesh mTLS
        Router->>ISVC2: Inference request<br/>HTTP/80, in-mesh mTLS
    end
    ISVC1-->>Router: Result A
    ISVC2-->>Router: Result B
    Router-->>Route: Combined result
    Route-->>Client: JSON Response

    participant LMCtrl as LocalModel Controller<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant LMAgent as LocalModelNode Agent
    participant Job as Download Job
    participant NodeFS as Node Filesystem (PV)

    Note over LMCtrl,NodeFS: Flow 4: LocalModel Cache Distribution
    LMCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create PV/PVC<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount
    LMAgent->>K8sAPI: Create download Job<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount
    Job->>Storage: Download model<br/>HTTPS/443, Credentials from Secret
    Storage-->>Job: Model artifacts
    Job->>NodeFS: Write to local PV<br/>Filesystem, POSIX permissions
